</script>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p><strong>Famous SAT Scores</strong></p>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p><em>How does your own SAT score stack up to public radio hosts, Federal Reserve chairs, and other famous Americans? Check out our wrap up below. (Note: before 2005, the SAT was on a 1600-point scale. The current version of the test is on a 2400-point scale.)</em></p>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p><strong>Kai Ryssdal</strong><span>, host of Marketplace: 1160 (Source: Kai Ryssdal)</span><br /><img src="http://www.marketplace.org/sites/default/files/styles/200x200/public/Kai%20Selfie.jpg" /></p>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p><strong> </strong></p>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p><strong>Ben Bernake</strong><span>, former Federal Reserve Chair: 1590 (</span><a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/investopedia/2013/10/22/the-legacy-of-ben-bernanke/" target="_blank">Forbes</a><span>)</span><br /><img src="http://www.marketplace.org/sites/default/files/styles/200x200/public/bernanke_dec12.jpg" /></p>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p><strong>Ryan Fitzpatrick</strong><span>, football player: 1580 (</span><a href="http://www.sportingnews.com/mlb/feed/2010-09/smart-athletes/story/sporting-news-names-the-20-smartest-athletes-in-sports" target="_blank">Sporting News</a><span>)</span><br /><img src="http://www.marketplace.org/sites/default/files/styles/200x200/public/null/451778675.jpg" /></p>"},{"content":"<p><strong>Scarlett Johansson</strong><span>, actress: 1080 (</span><a href="http://www.interviewmagazine.com/film/scarlett-johansson-oct-2013#page2" target="_blank">Interview Magazine</a><span>)</span><br /><img src="http://www.marketplace.org/sites/default/files/styles/200x200/public/52252348.jpg?" /></p>","type":"text/html"},{"content":"<p><strong>Chuck Schumer</strong><span>, Senator from New York: 1600 (</span><a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/campaigns/keyraces98/stories/ny100598.htm" target="_bla